  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhanced Collective Capacity to Assist Vulnerable Migrants in Chad</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to address the urgent protection needs of vulnerable and stranded migrants in Chad through direct assistance, reinforcing the capacity of existing local service providers and improving identification of victims of trafficking by training law enforcement officials and the gendarmerie. Migrants in vulnerable situations will have access to direct assistance including food, water, non-food items and shelter. IOM will also provide tailored protection services (psychosocial counselling support, medical assistance and/or livelihood support for those that require them). The capacities of key Chadian service providers (notably the Ndjamena Airport and medical clinics in Faya and Moussoro) will be improved through the equipment or rehabilitation of their premises to create safer spaces for direct assistance. The capacities of law enforcement officials (notably the police, the judicial police, border authorities and the gendarmerie) will also be enhanced to enable a better understanding of the relevant legal frameworks at national and local levels, and of identification tools and referral mechanisms in line with international human rights law and protection principles.</narrative>
  </description>
